      "writtenOn": "2026-04-02T10:15:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The msg is fully zeroed so the multicast count bytes are already 0, but len doesn\u0027t cover them. Per the virtio spec §5.1.6.5.2.2 [1], the driver MUST send two tables, eg.\n\n    len \u003d sizeof (mac_table-\u003eentries) + mac_table-\u003eentries * sizeof (mac_table-\u003emacs[0]);                                                                                          \n    len +\u003d sizeof (u32); /* empty multicast table, already zeroed by memset */                                                                                                     \n\nSame issue in virtio_pci_remove_mac_filter.\n[1] https://docs.oasis-open.org/virtio/virtio/v1.2/virtio-v1.2.html#x1-2520002",
      "revId": "b0408bb92b7ca3cabd78dcc2fcc8d20014b7d202",
